Understate: The claim may be understating the amount of Wisconsin's coronavirus funding that has been spent by only mentioning the 3.8% figure without considering expenses already incurred or funds already committed to programs and response efforts.

Problematic assumption: The claim may make the problematic assumption that the unaccounted portion of the coronavirus funding is entirely unspent, without considering other possible uses or obligations of the funds.
